    "It is then again easy to to show that the Hartree-Fock Hamiltonian in terms of the c operators is again diagonal in k and s, i.e.HHF τ ask α,τ ′ bs ′ k β = δ ss ′ δ k α,k β HHF τ a,τ ′ s (k α, s) (104)57 In a numerical calculation with a discrete momentum grid set by N 1, N 2, we typically require that q IVC also lies on this grid.",
    "This is so that we can directly compare calculations performed with different values of q IVC.",
